node.text: A new survey finds that a rising share of Americans say things in the US are going badly and that the economy is in poor shape, with increased worries about the coronavirus, the economy and crime.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Emma Raducanu and Leylah Fernandez will make history in all-teen US Open final தக584 င CNN'.

node.text:
This year's US Open women's final will be the first major final between teens since the 1999 US Open, when Serena Williams defeated Martina Hingis. Britain's Emma Raducanu, 18, will face Canada's Leylah Fernandez, 19, on Saturday.⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)

May be an image of map and text that says 'Afghanistan is now one of very few countries with no women in top government ranks Share of women in high-ranking ministerial positions Jan. 2021 (%) 12 24 35 59 No data 46 Afghanistan Jan 2021 6.5% New Sept. government 0%'.

node.text:
Prior to the Taliban’s takeover, two women served in senior ministerial positions — just 6.5% of the government. Now, there are no women serving in high-ranking positions in the country’s new interim government.⁠
⁠
These countries currently have no women serving in high-ranking positions in government: Azerbaijan, Armenia, Brunei, North Korea, Papua New Guinea, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines, Saudi Arabia, Thailand, Tuvalu, Vanuatu, Vietnam and Yemen, according to the most recent IPU data.⁠
⁠
Note: The dataset includes ministers, deputy heads of government and heads of government when they held ministerial portfolios; heads of public agencies are excluded. Members of parliament are not part of the dataset. UN data is not available for some territories.⁠
⁠
Source: UN Women/Inter-Parliamentary Union ⁠
(January 1, 2021)

For 10 days, Gary Crane stood outside of his wife's ICU room holding up a sign that said, "I love you." "She's worth it, and I just wanted her to know that I was rooting for her," he said. Donna, his wife, recovered, and now the couple is urging people to get vaccinated so they can avoid what they went through.

(📸: Gary and Donna Crane)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says '14.8% That's how many households with kids face food insecurity Source: US Department of Agriculture, 2020 CNN'.

node.text:
Food insecurity among families with children rose in 2020 as the coronavirus pandemic upended the US economy, according to a US Department of Agriculture report released Wednesday. ⁠
⁠
Some 60 million people — or 1 in 5 US residents — received charitable food assistance in 2020, an increase of 50% from the year before, said Emily Engelhard, managing director of research at Feeding America, the nation's largest domestic hunger relief organization.

⁠

node.text: The California recall election is about a week away. The rules are many, detailed and confusing, but the bottom line is that if any less than half of the voters who take part oppose the recall of Gov. Gavin Newsom, he'll be out of office. The top vote-getter of the 46 candidates to replace Newsom, no matter how few votes that person gets, will be in.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 08, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, monument and text that says 'A Black man's statue is the only monument standing on Virginia's historic Monument Avenue C P CNN'.

node.text:
A towering statue of Confederate Gen. Robert E. Lee was the last Confederate statue to be removed from historic Monument Avenue in Richmond, Virginia. Now, a statue of Black tennis legend Arthur Ashe is the lone monument still standing on the street in the former capital of the Confederacy. Ashe was born in Richmond and shattered records in the sport and championed civil rights.⁠
⁠
(📸: Steve Helber/AP)
